39:23.195 --> 39:26.278
— No?
— Mm.

39:28.408 --> 39:30.114
Careful.

39:30.244 --> 39:32.235
You're all right, Davis.

39:33.914 --> 39:35.950
— l have to admit something.
— Uh—oh.

39:36.083 --> 39:38.825
No, no, no, no. I need to say this.

39:39.753 --> 39:41.254
l have a confession to make.

39:41.380 --> 39:44.372
I did call the police that time last summer

39:44.508 --> 39:47.625
when you were rehearsing
the brass band on the first floor.

39:47.761 --> 39:51.379
- That was me.
— Dude, don't worry on it.

39:51.515 --> 39:53.426
You called the cops

39:53.559 --> 39:56.096
for loud music in the Treme?

39:56.228 --> 39:58.059
Bygones, bygones.

39:58.188 --> 39:59.473
I didn't know he did it.

39:59.606 --> 40:02.348
I had nothing whatsoever to do with that.

40:02.484 --> 40:05.066
Any other secrets you'd like
to unburden yourself of?

40:05.195 --> 40:07.106
Don, lighten up!

40:07.239 --> 40:09.605
- It's bygones.
— Come on, baby.

40:09.741 --> 40:11.993
No fighting, no fighting.

41:05.339 --> 41:08.331
God, Allan, I cannot believe
you would just lie to me like that.

41:08.467 --> 41:12.130
— I don't know who I'm living with anymore.
- It's a vale of tears.

41:14.931 --> 41:16.182
Henry.

41:17.851 --> 41:20.342
(Laughs) Hey, darlin'. Where you been at?

41:20.479 --> 41:24.222
Party's spent.
A good one, though, while it lasted.

41:24.358 --> 41:26.895
Party? ls Davis still up?

41:27.027 --> 41:29.814
Still up, still crazy.

41:45.879 --> 41:49.371
| just knew something
was gonna come through for me tonight.

41:49.508 --> 41:51.294
Something?

41:51.426 --> 41:53.542
Someone.

41:53.679 --> 41:55.886
You had a party, Davis?

41:56.014 --> 41:58.551
You didn't invite me.

41:58.684 --> 42:02.051
(Sighs) Oh. Uh...

42:05.899 --> 42:10.609
Well, you had your gig at Bacchanal

42:10.737 --> 42:14.025
and l didn't...| didn't want you to be upset.

42:16.535 --> 42:19.527
Yeah, my gig at Bacchanal...

42:20.997 --> 42:23.909
— (Rain pattering)
- What's wrong?

42:27.462 --> 42:29.953
(Clears throat) You have class today?

42:30.090 --> 42:32.627
Freshman lit, my calling.

42:32.759 --> 42:34.624
lthought that was an 11 o'clock.

42:34.761 --> 42:36.297
I'm not leaving yet.

42:36.430 --> 42:39.297
l have some things in the office
I need to do before I go.

42:39.433 --> 42:41.424
Dad could drop me off
at school later.

42:41.560 --> 42:45.098
It's not like we're doing anything
important in first period anyway.

42:45.230 --> 42:47.141
None of it's important according to you.

42:47.274 --> 42:48.980
— You're coming with me.
— Dad.

42:49.109 --> 42:51.475
Better listen to your mom.

42:55.198 --> 42:58.315
— (He growls)
- (Laughs)

42:59.578 --> 43:01.489
Mm.

43:01.621 --> 43:04.033
You all right, Cray?

43:04.166 --> 43:06.873
Well, once more into the breach.

43:09.296 --> 43:10.661
Hey, Sof!

43:10.797 --> 43:13.413
Sweetie, Daddy.

43:15.343 --> 43:18.176
— l...|just...
—What?

43:18.305 --> 43:21.513
| just wanted to tell you
you look very pretty today.

43:21.641 --> 43:23.506
Really nice.

43:23.643 --> 43:26.180
- (Kisses)
— Thanks, Daddy.

43:26.313 --> 43:27.974
— Enjoy your day.
- I will.

43:32.652 --> 43:34.608
— Hey, Toni.
— Huh?

43:34.738 --> 43:36.979
Kick a little ass today.

43:37.115 --> 43:38.776
(Laughs)

43:43.121 --> 43:46.488
— You buckled up?
- (Engine starts)

43:50.170 --> 43:53.333
— (Davis) Mm, morning.
- Hm.

43:55.926 --> 43:58.042
I'm sorry about your night.

43:59.721 --> 44:01.803
(She sighs)

44:01.932 --> 44:03.923
I'm glad you ended it here, though.

44:04.059 --> 44:06.516
No, don't be.

44:06.645 --> 44:09.011
The thunderstorm cleared things up for me.

44:10.440 --> 44:13.307
There'll be other opportunities.

44:13.443 --> 44:16.526
I know that, but not here.

44:16.655 --> 44:19.613
Ugh, not that again.

44:20.534 --> 44:24.118
— You can't...you can't be serious.
- Mm, I am.

44:25.831 --> 44:28.868
You're a damn good chef.

44:29.000 --> 44:33.084
I am better than good,
but this town beat me.

44:34.089 --> 44:36.421
As much as I love it,

44:36.550 --> 44:38.962
I'm not trying to fight with it anymore.

44:42.180 --> 44:45.047
But New York?

44:45.183 --> 44:48.892
I wanna see how I stack up
against the big boys, you know?

44:49.938 --> 44:52.224
Without all these...

44:52.357 --> 44:55.269
these broke—ass levees

44:55.402 --> 44:58.394
— and blocked gas lines and...
- Hey.

45:00.240 --> 45:04.950
May | quote the author of
La Cuisine Creole?

45:05.078 --> 45:07.114
I believe it's your professional bible.

45:07.247 --> 45:09.078
Jesus, Davis, do you ever stop?

45:09.207 --> 45:12.574
New York is very fashionable and fast,

45:12.711 --> 45:15.293
so fast you can't even stroll through it.

45:15.422 --> 45:17.788
You just get pushed along.

45:17.924 --> 45:20.586
And don't plan on getting invited
to any backyard barbecues

45:20.719 --> 45:23.131
— because there ain't no backyards.
- You don't know that.

45:23.263 --> 45:27.723
Everyone dressed in business suits,
working, working, working.

45:27.851 --> 45:30.183
Of course the, uh...what do you call it?

45:30.312 --> 45:32.894
— The financials are very strong.
— Davis.

45:36.943 --> 45:39.150
or a four—hour lunch?

45:39.279 --> 45:41.941
Would you rather have a Macy's Day Parade

45:42.073 --> 45:44.234
with fucking Bullwinkle floats...

45:45.577 --> 45:48.785
or an impromptu second line

45:48.914 --> 45:52.122
where you dance your ass off
with your neighbors?

45:53.668 --> 45:56.956
Is your check from the tourism board
in the mail?

46:08.433 --> 46:10.094
There are so many...

46:12.896 --> 46:15.308
beautiful moments here.

46:17.734 --> 46:19.645
They're just moments.

46:21.696 --> 46:24.688
They're not a life.

46:31.247 --> 46:33.203
You about to sit there all day?

46:33.333 --> 46:36.700
- What else I'm gonna do?
— Well, we could use a little help.

46:36.836 --> 46:39.327
See if you can do better
on a job than the last time.

46:39.464 --> 46:40.670
What's the job?

46:40.799 --> 46:43.165
I got a rack of supplies
I gotta pick up at Home Depot,

46:43.301 --> 46:45.792
store here in the bar...gypsum and alum.

46:45.929 --> 46:49.513
— What's that?
— Raw materials for plaster.

46:52.310 --> 46:55.802
— Boy, you wanna make some coin or what?
- I ain't seen nothing yet,

46:55.939 --> 46:58.726
after all that work I did
helping him with that suit.

46:59.526 --> 47:03.189
You do my lifting for me,
you'll get a little something today.

47:03.947 --> 47:05.357
All right.

47:08.868 --> 47:13.407
Shit, I don't know which one of you two
I feel more sorry for.

47:16.543 --> 47:18.579
(Chuckles)

47:18.712 --> 47:22.045
"She was blindly following
whatever impulse moved her

47:22.173 --> 47:26.758
"as if she had placed herself
in alien hands for direction

47:26.886 --> 47:29.878
"and freed her soul of responsibility."

47:30.015 --> 47:31.551
OK, Ben?

47:31.683 --> 47:34.015
I'm just trying to put this book
into perspective.

47:34.144 --> 47:37.682
Is The Awakening the first
women's lib novel or something?

47:37.814 --> 47:38.929
I wouldn't...

47:39.065 --> 47:43.024
No, to label it as such
would be to ghettoize a great work.

47:43.153 --> 47:45.565
(Gwyneth) Well, what happens to Edna was...

47:45.697 --> 47:48.109
I thought it was really depressing.

47:48.241 --> 47:50.277
No, no.

47:50.410 --> 47:52.947
This isn't a feminist manifesto.

47:53.079 --> 47:58.619
This book is not about Edna's emancipation from male
authority,

47:58.752 --> 48:02.461
and the ending of the book

48:02.589 --> 48:04.750
is not the end.

48:04.883 --> 48:09.126
It is a transition,

48:09.262 --> 48:13.972
a rejection of disappointment and failure.

48:14.100 --> 48:16.432
The farther Edna walks away

48:16.561 --> 48:19.098
from the constraints
of society and convention,

48:19.230 --> 48:20.766
the more free she becomes.

48:20.899 --> 48:24.812
She's not moving toward the darkness.

48:24.944 --> 48:28.357
She's embracing spiritual liberation.

48:38.458 --> 48:40.494
I'm gonna let y'all go early today.

48:40.627 --> 48:44.165
— (Girl) All right!
— Go out and read. It's a glorious day.

48:44.297 --> 48:45.878
(Students chattering)

48:50.553 --> 48:52.544
(Girl) Thank God.

48:55.350 --> 48:57.341
(Boy) You the man, teach.

48:58.228 --> 49:00.014
(Sonny) J‘ Come on, baby

49:00.146 --> 49:01.477
J‘ Let me show you where it's at

49:01.606 --> 49:05.144
J‘ Oh, come on

49:05.276 --> 49:09.019
J‘ The name of the place, I like it like that

49:09.155 --> 49:13.068
J‘ Yeah, there's a place across the track

49:13.201 --> 49:14.816
J‘ The name of the place

49:14.953 --> 49:16.489
J‘ ls I like it like that J‘

49:18.206 --> 49:19.912
(Grunting)

49:29.342 --> 49:32.800
It's called "work." Get used to it.

49:32.929 --> 49:36.046
Your back's gonna hurt
for the next 40, 50 years.

49:40.520 --> 49:43.853
Hey, I should at least get a beer
at the end of the day like y'all, right?

49:43.982 --> 49:46.473
We got one more stop to make. Let's go.

49:48.820 --> 49:50.435
What's it gonna be, then, boss?

49:50.572 --> 49:53.188
A bowl of gumbo, barbecue shrimp po' boy

49:53.324 --> 49:55.315
and another Abita Amber.

49:55.451 --> 49:57.362
That's what I like to hear.

49:57.495 --> 49:59.827
Nothing like Liuzza's, huh?

49:59.956 --> 50:03.369
Some say this one's better
than the other one on Bienville.

50:05.545 --> 50:08.002
The Pope in Avignon.

50:14.596 --> 50:16.928
(Darius) Those army dudes?

50:17.056 --> 50:19.923
(Albert) Just back from active duty in Iraq.

50:20.059 --> 50:22.436
I heard a rumor they were down here now.

50:22.562 --> 50:25.269
Wanted to see it for myself.

50:25.398 --> 50:28.765
So? You ain't changed nothing
doing what you did.

50:28.902 --> 50:31.018
Lost a battle is all.

50:31.154 --> 50:33.110
But sometimes the battles worth fighting

50:33.239 --> 50:35.321
are the ones you know you're gonna lose.

50:36.284 --> 50:38.525
Those cops, they know who you are.

50:38.661 --> 50:40.947
You see the way they keep looking at you?

50:41.080 --> 50:44.789
— Uh—huh.
— But you could get locked up again.

50:46.085 --> 50:48.667
They gonna do what they gonna do.

50:48.796 --> 50:51.924
Me, I'm gonna be heard.

50:52.050 --> 50:54.837
So that's why you wanna mask?

51:00.433 --> 51:02.173
Mm—hm.

51:06.105 --> 51:08.437
(Ship's horn blaring)

51:25.458 --> 51:27.995
I love me some Fess,
but it don't go so easily with violin.

51:28.127 --> 51:31.335
Jambalaya. I'll do Gatemouth.

51:31.464 --> 51:33.830
— (Chuckles)
- One, two.

52:10.169 --> 52:12.160
(J‘ Music on radio)

52:27.353 --> 52:29.218
Oh!

52:29.355 --> 52:31.266
So happy to see you.

52:54.839 --> 52:59.674
100 more from last night's gig, for Daymo.

53:00.970 --> 53:04.588
- Who the fuck is you?
— You can pay me back when you can.

53:04.724 --> 53:07.761
I called Larry last night.
He wiring the rest of the money today.

53:07.894 --> 53:11.637
— (Loud banging)
— Oh. Well, that's good.

53:11.773 --> 53:14.310
I know he glad he could help.

53:14.442 --> 53:16.433
(Banging continues)

53:17.737 --> 53:22.026
- You not gonna open up today?
— Why bother, with all that noise?

53:22.158 --> 53:24.945
Tell you what,
that boy's a workhorse, though.

53:25.078 --> 53:27.285
Shouldn't be all that much longer
before he's done.

53:29.082 --> 53:30.913
It's all gonna work out.

53:32.043 --> 53:34.329
You'll see.

53:35.463 --> 53:37.454
(J‘ Violin playing)

53:55.608 --> 53:57.314
Are you sure?

53:58.528 --> 54:00.519
Always for pleasure, dear.

54:36.649 --> 54:38.435
Can I burn one of those from you?

54:38.568 --> 54:41.310
- They're reds.
— All the better.

54:55.001 --> 54:59.335
Don't ever let anyone tell you to quit.
These are wonderful.

55:00.756 --> 55:02.747
Obliged.

55:04.510 --> 55:07.502
- (Birds squawking)
— (J‘ Organ music playing)

56:12.954 --> 56:15.696
— Where are you headed?
- My place.

56:15.831 --> 56:18.243
Where's that?

56:19.001 --> 56:20.912
You want me to walk with you?

56:21.045 --> 56:24.663
I'll be OK. It's just a couple of blocks.

56:26.133 --> 56:29.500
I hope we, uh, play together again. Night.

56:43.609 --> 56:46.396
What exactly is a dependent clause?

56:46.529 --> 56:49.987
You're asking the wrong person.
That's your father's department.

56:50.116 --> 56:54.280
But I need to turn this in tomorrow.
Where is he?

56:54.412 --> 56:57.370
I tried to call. He's not answering his cell.

56:59.834 --> 57:02.041
Probably just out ofjuice.

57:02.169 --> 57:04.546
You know how he forgets to charge it.

57:12.138 --> 57:14.254
(Buoy bell clanging)

57:14.390 --> 57:17.132
(Ship's horn blaring)
